h2.span: Overall issues and pull requests status

div.div: Created new branch refactor in shinyPy/webnovel-translator

Refactor chapter upload processing and introduce ChapterChunk model
- Updated ProcessChapterUpload job to improve error handling and logging. - Removed unused TranslationProject model reference and streamlined chapter creation. - Introduced ChapterChunk model to manage chapter segments with status tracking. - Enhanced FileProcessorService to support various file types and improved text extraction logic. - Updated User model to include subscription management methods and statistics. - Refactored useAuth hook to manage user authentication state and subscription data more effectively. - Adjusted API response types and user-related types for better clarity and structure. - Cleaned up frontend components to reflect changes in user and subscription management.

feat: Add pages for glossaries, projects, project details, subscription, login, and registration
- Implemented GlossariesPage for managing translation glossaries. - Created LoginPage for user authentication. - Developed ProjectDetailPage to view project details and manage chapters. - Added ProjectsPage for managing translation projects. - Implemented RegisterPage for user registration. - Created SubscriptionPage for managing user subscriptions and upgrade options.
feat: Implement API service for authentication, projects, chapters, glossaries, and subscriptions
- Added ApiService to handle API requests for user authentication, project management, glossary management, and subscription handling. - Implemented methods for user registration, login, logout, and fetching user details. - Added methods for managing translation projects, chapters, and glossaries.
feat: Define types for user, projects, chapters, glossaries, and API responses
- Created TypeScript interfaces for User, TranslationProject, Chapter, Glossary, AuthResponse, UserSubscription, and more. - Defined types for API responses and pagination.
chore: Set up API routes for authentication, projects, chapters, glossaries, and subscriptions
- Defined API routes for user registration, login, logout, and fetching user details. - Set up routes for managing translation projects, chapters, glossaries, and subscriptions.
Add ProcessChapterUpload job and Glossary model with methods for term management

Add Docker configuration for development environment
- Created docker-compose.dev.yml to define services for PostgreSQL, Redis, backend, and frontend. - Added .dockerignore file in the frontend directory to exclude unnecessary files from the Docker context. - Implemented Dockerfile for the frontend service to set up the Node.js environment and run the development server.
